ributed to social worker involvement in policy change in the social work discourse and education in different countries?’ and ‘how do social workers influence social policy in various national settings?’ These issues are relevant to social worker practitioners, students, educators and researchers, as well as to social policy scholars, who are interested in the role of professionals in social policy formulation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSocial policy. 0aSocial service. 0aSocial workers. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aCampanini, Annamaria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFacchini, Carla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGal, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGal, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoefer, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIarskaia-Smirnova, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez-Román, María-Asunción, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendes, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomanov, Pavel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalonen, Tapio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThorén, Katarina H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiss-Gal, Idit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiss-Gal, Idit, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-